<TITLE> 20 hurt in BCL violence at Mymensingh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mymensingh, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com)  At least 20 people were injured, including police, as clashes erupted between two factions of Chhatra League at the Bangladesh Agriculture University campus on Sunday. Police were forced to use blank fire and tear gas to control the situation, and arrested nine students in connection with the violence. Mymensing additional police superintendent ASM Akhtaruzzaman told bdnews24.com that the violence sparked off at around 2pm between two groups of students led by Chhatra League's BAU branch president and general secretary. "They were fighting for domination on campus," said the police official. Chaos spread across the campus amid "chases and counter-chases" of the clashing groups, said police and witnesses. At least 20 people were injured, including Kotwali Police Station's officer in charge and three constables, said Akhtaruzzaman. Three among the injured were taken to Mymensing Medical College Hospital. Extra police force had been deployed to the area, he added. bdnews2
